posts.name: Caitlin
posts.cooked: Does your team take the time to tint the polycarb or do you actually purchase tinted polycarb? It’s a painful process tinting so just asking what others do

posts.name: Joe Schmo
posts.cooked: I think we just buy ours pre-tinted. I didn’t actually know people tinted it themselves.

posts.name: Stewart Riley
posts.cooked: Given that the tinting process uses fairly toxic dyes, I’d never let my students anywhere near it. We buy smoke grey polycarb when we want something besides clear and let it go at that.

posts.name: Alex Cormier
posts.cooked: Ask for smoked polycarb from your supplier. Easily worth the extra$.

posts.cooked: Teams I have worked with have either purchased tinted poly or painted it themselves.  Painting was actually pretty cool as the side that gets then paint was flat while the opposite side was really glossy.
